      "source": [
        "**Compare Thresholds 0.30 vs 0.40 vs 0.50**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "f2QsheVoJzpB"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Random Forest doesn’t directly “decide” diabetes until we choose a cutoff probability.\n",
        "\n",
        "Default cutoff is 0.50\n",
        "\n",
        "But in healthcare, we prefer to catch more diabetic patients\n",
        "\n",
        "So we test different cutoffs:\n",
        "\n",
        "0.30 = more sensitive (catches more, but more false alarms)\n",
        "\n",
        "0.40 = balanced (often good)\n",
        "\n",
        "0.50 = stricter (fewer false alarms, but misses more diabetics)\n",
        "\n",
        "“We tuned threshold to match healthcare goal (reduce false negatives).”"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "P7UUl3-gJ-IN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, classification_report\n",
        "\n",
        "# probabilities for diabetes class (1)\n",
        "y_prob_rf = rf_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
        "\n",
        "for t in [0.30, 0.40, 0.50]:\n",
        "    y_pred_t = (y_prob_rf >= t).astype(int)\n",
        "    print(f\"\\n--- Threshold = {t} ---\")\n",
        "    print(\"Confusion Matrix:\")\n",
        "    print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_t))\n",
        "    print(\"\\nClassification Report:\")\n",
        "    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_t))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
