      "source": [
        "SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) was applied to interpret the Random Forest model and understand how each feature influences diabetes predictions. The SHAP summary plot shows that features such as age and hypertension significantly impact the model’s output. Higher values of these features tend to push predictions toward the diabetic class, while lower values push predictions toward the non-diabetic class. This explainability step improves transparency and helps understand how different health indicators contribute to diabetes risk."
